    "excerpt": "A pizmon for calling up a (male) Jew-by-choice for his first aliyah to the Torah after completing his conversion process. (Pizmonim for female and non-binary Jews-by-choice forthcoming!) To be recited before the blessing, led by the gabbai with the community responding with the refrain. . . .",
    "content": "<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\nA pizmon for calling up a (male) Jew-by-choice for his first aliyah to the Torah after completing his conversion process. (Pizmonim for female and non-binary Jews-by-choice forthcoming!) To be recited before the blessing, led by the gabbai with the community responding with the refrain.\n</div>\n<hr />\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Source (Hebrew)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Translation (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">אַ</span>בְרָהָם הוּא אָבִֽיךָ אִמְּךָ הִיא שָׂרָה.<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">A</span>vraham is your father, your mother is Sarah.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> The parents of all Israel, traditionally stated to be the parents of all converts as well.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> M. Sotah 7:8, the declaration of the people Israel when Agrippas, the descendant of converts, came up to read Torah at the haqhel ceremony. This declaration is the refrain of the entire pizmon.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">בָּ</span>רוּךְ הַמְּקַבֵּל עֹל מִצְוֺת הַתּוֹרָה.<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">B</span>lessed be the reciever of the yoke of the Torah’s commandments.<br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">גָּ</span>ר כָּאֶזְרָח כֵּן כָּתוּב בַּמִּקְרָא.<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">C</span>onvert like native, is written in Scripture.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Find Lev. 19:34&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">דַּ</span>ם בְּרִית הִטַּֽפְתָּ לַמִּילָה הַטְּהוֹרָה.<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">D</span>ripping covenant-blood for the pure circumcision.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> This can refer to a full circumcision or the hatafat dam brit ceremony where a convert who had already been circumcised merely has a drop of blood taken from his penis. This verse would require a major rewrite for a feminine or gender-neutral version. Feel free to suggest  your own — remember it has to start with daleth and end with -rah!&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">הֵ</span>״א מִיּוֹ״ד הֵ״א לַקּוֹנֶה הַמְּעָרָה.<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">E</span>ntering hei from yod-hei for the cave-purchaser.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_5');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_5');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[5]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_5\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Avraham, who was named Avram before his conversion. According to the Zohar, Lekh Lekha 35:454-457, the heis added to Avram and Sarai to make them Avraham and Sarah came from the Divine Name itself.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_5', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">וָ</span>י״ו הֵ״א נָתַן הֵ״א לָאֵם וְהוֹרָה.<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">F</span>rom vav-hei was hei given to the mother and parent.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_6');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_6');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[6]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_6\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Sarah, who was named Sarai before her conversion.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_6', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">זְ</span>כׇר־נָא עַמִּי אַל־תִּלְחַץ פֶּן־יִקְרָא.<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">G</span>ive no oppression, my people, remember, lest he call out!<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_7');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_7');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[7]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_7\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Find Exodus 23:9 and Deut. 24:14-15.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_7', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">ח</span>וֹבֵב הַגֵּרִים הַגִּבּוֹר וְנוֹרָא.<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">H</span>ow the Mighty and Awesome one cherishes the convert!<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_8');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_8');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[8]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_8\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Find Deut. 10:17-18&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_8', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">טֻ</span>מְאָתְךָ הִשְׁלַֽחְתָּ בִּטְבִילָה בָּרָה.<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">I</span>n a pure dipping<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_9');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_9');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[9]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_9\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Referring to the miqveh that converts go through as part of their process.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_9', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> you cast off your impurity.<br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">יְ</span>הוּדִי אַתָּה בְּשִׂמְחָה וְאוֹרָה.<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">J</span>ewish are you, in happiness and light!<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_10');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_10');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[10]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_10\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Find Esth. 8:16&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_10', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">כֵּ</span>ן עֲמֹד פלוני בֶּן־אַבְרָהָם עוֹלֶה לַתּוֹרָה!<br />\nאָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה! אָחִֽינוּ אַתָּה!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">K</span>insman (<span class=\"instruction\">name:</span> ___) son of Abraham, stand, ascending to the Torah!<br />\nYou are our brother! You are our brother!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\">Notes</span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" style=\"display: none;; display: none;\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\"></span></p></div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container__1\" style=\"\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">Notes</caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >1</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">The parents of all Israel, traditionally stated to be the parents of all converts as well.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >2</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">M. Sotah 7:8, the declaration of the people Israel when Agrippas, the descendant of converts, came up to read Torah at the haqhel ceremony. This declaration is the refrain of the entire pizmon.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >3</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Find Lev. 19:34</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >4</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">This can refer to a full circumcision or the hatafat dam brit ceremony where a convert who had already been circumcised merely has a drop of blood taken from his penis. This verse would require a major rewrite for a feminine or gender-neutral version. Feel free to suggest  your own — remember it has to start with daleth and end with -rah!</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >5</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Avraham, who was named Avram before his conversion. According to the Zohar, Lekh Lekha 35:454-457, the heis added to Avram and Sarai to make them Avraham and Sarah came from the Divine Name itself.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >6</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Sarah, who was named Sarai before her conversion.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >7</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Find Exodus 23:9 and Deut. 24:14-15.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_8\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >8</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Find Deut. 10:17-18</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_9\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >9</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Referring to the miqveh that converts go through as part of their process.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_10\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >10</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Find Esth. 8:16</td></tr>\r\n\r\n </tbody> </table> </div></div><script type=\"text/javascript\"> function footnote_expand_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').show(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('−'); } function footnote_collapse_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').hide(); jQu